    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I can certainly expand the \"Prohibited Use\" section to address sneaky behaviors like hiding phones under desks, in pockets, or using them discreetly, which are often the most disruptive.\n\nHere is the revised policy section:\n\n**Revised Section 2: Prohibited Use and \"Hidden\" Distractions**\n\nDuring all instructional periods, students are strictly prohibited from using cell phones for any purpose other than direct teacher-requested educational tasks. This prohibition explicitly encompasses \"hidden\" or \"sneaky\" usage, including but not limited to:\n*   Storing phones under desks, in backpacks without permission, or in pockets while the device is switched on or capable of being activated.\n*   Using vibration modes to receive notifications.\n*   Taking photos, videos, or screenshots of the board or classroom materials.\n*   Using apps that emit light or sound to distract peers.\n*   Any attempt to bypass the \"Silent Mode\" requirement by using headphones or earbuds to listen to music or audio content.\n\n**Enforcement of Hidden Violations**\nIf a teacher observes a student hiding a phone or engaging in the behaviors listed above:\n1.  **Immediate Confiscation:** The",
